# MVC Structure

Follow this on **every** feature, fix, and refactor. Do not dump logic into `App.jsx` or `server/index.js`.

## Server (`server/`)

| Layer | Folder | Responsibility |
|-------|--------|----------------|
| Model | `models/` | DB queries and data access |
| Controller | `controllers/` | Request handling, call models, shape responses |
| Routes | `routes/` | Wire HTTP paths to controllers only |
| Config | `config/` | DB and env setup |
| Utils | `utils/` | Shared helpers |

Flow: `routes` → `controllers` → `models`

## Client (`src/`)

| Layer | Folder | Responsibility |
|-------|--------|----------------|
| View | `views/` | Presentational UI only (JSX, styling, props) |
| Controller | `controllers/` | Hooks: state, events, call models — no JSX |
| Model | `models/` | API calls, static data access, client data sources |
| Config | `config/` | API base URL and client config |
| Utils | `utils/` | Shared helpers |

Flow: `views` → `controllers` → `models` → API (or local data)

## Mandatory checklist (every prompt)

1. New feature → matching files in the correct layers (model + controller + view/route as needed).
2. Views: no `fetch`, no business rules, no data lists hardcoded — receive data via props/hooks from controllers.
3. Controllers: no SQL, no JSX/HTML markup.
4. Models: no HTTP status codes (server), no JSX (client). Static lists/config data belong in models (e.g. `getNavModules`), not controllers.
5. Prefer extending this layout over one-off folders at the root of `src/` or `server/`.

## Examples

```text
✅ src/models/navModel.js        → getNavModules()
✅ src/controllers/navController.js → useNavModules() calls model, holds active id
✅ src/views/layout/ModuleNav.jsx → renders modules from props

❌ NAV_MODULES array inside a controller
❌ fetch() inside a view
❌ route handlers inside server/index.js
```
